en_189751_0	The government declares today (May 02) as a day of mourning in recognition of the service rendered by the late Dr. Lester James Peiris to the cinema.
en_189751_1	The funeral of the legendary Sri Lankan filmmaker will be held today with full state patronage at Independence Square from 4 pm onwards.
en_189751_2	Dr. Lester James Peiris, who is credited with revolutionizing Sinhala cinema in the 1950s, passed away in Colombo on Sunday at the age of 99.
en_189751_3	The funeral committee noted that renowned film director Adur Gopalsinham of Kerala who was a friend of Dr. Lester James Peiris is to arrive in the island today.
en_189751_4	The remains of late Dr. Lester James Peiris will be placed until 10 am today at his residence located in Colombo 5.
en_189751_5	Following religious proceedings, the remains would be brought to the Colombo Independence square and will be open to the public to pay their final respects from 12 noon to 3 pm.
